        Streamwalker is three meters ahead, moving with patient grace.
        Streamwalker says, "Feel the river. It wants to help. Not all water fights."

        Brightbloom bounces along the bank, tracking my progress.
        Brightbloom says, "Very philosophical! But true! This river is friendly! Territorial agreement includes maintained safe crossings!"

        I take another step; the stone wobbles slightly and my stomach drops
        Streamwalker says, "Center your weightlike roots finding ground. The stone holds."

        I adjust; the wobble steadies and I breathe.

        Brightbloom says, "See? You've got it! Natural talent!"
        Brightbloom's flowers are blooming so enthusiastically they look like they might launch right off the bush.

        The water reaches my waist, cold but not freezing. The current is stronger here, but Streamwalker has been rightit pushes me toward the crossing path, not away from it. Like the river knows where travelers should go.

        Scout bobs happily nearby, occasionally bouncing on the surface and sending up small splashes.

        Brightbloom announces, "Halfway! Excellent progress! Very steady! Much better than the traveler who panicked and tried to swim upstreamdon't do that, by the way, never ends well"
        Streamwalker says to Brightbloom, "Brightbloom."
        Brightbloom replies, "Right! Staying positive! You're doing wonderfully, Kira!"

        I keep movingstep, find the stone, balance, step again. The rhythm is familiarnot so different from walking all day through Territory One. Find your pace. Trust the guides. Keep going.

        The water begins to recedethighs, then knees, then ankles.

        I step onto the far bank, dripping and cold but steady.

        Streamwalker has emerged meters ahead, their vines already gathering themselves back into traveling formation.
        Streamwalker says, "Excellent crossing. The river welcomed you."

        Brightbloom says, "*THAT WAS PERFECT!* First crossing with new guides and you handled it like an experienced traveler! Wait until the Territory Three team hears about this!"

        Scout bounces enthusiastically, flinging water droplets everywhere.

        I start laughing. I'm soaked, cold, my boots are full of river water, and I'd just crossed a river on an alien planet guided by a musical vine-plant and an overly enthusiastic bush.

        And I'd done it. Just done it. Without panicking or falling or needing rescue.

        ¶

        Buddy offers, "The water adds about two kilograms to your clothing weight. I recommend wringing out excess moisture when possible to reduce carrying load"
        I reply, "In a minute, Buddy. Let me have this moment."

        Buddy says, "Your heart rate suggests positive emotional response! Accomplishment releases dopamine"
        I say, "Buddy."
        Buddy says, "Recording moment for wellness documentation!"

        Streamwalker makes a gentle sighing sound.
        Streamwalker says, "There's sun ahead. We'll dry as we walk. The wetlands give and take water freely."
      </text>
